  <refnamediv>
    <refname>affine2d</refname>
    <refpurpose>Creates an affine2d object for input 3x3 matrix.</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Calling Sequence</title>
   <synopsis>
   y = affine2d(mat)
   
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry><term>mat :</term>
      <listitem><para> It is a 3x3 matrix which specifies forward affine2d transformation.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>y :</term>
      <listitem><para> an affine2d object with similar properties as the input.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
y = affine2d(mat) returns the affine2d object where a 3x3 numeric matrix is given as input
It encapsulates 2d affine geometri transformation.
   </para>
   <para>
</para>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Examples</title>
   <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
a=[1 2 0;3 4 0;5 1 1];
y=affine2d(a);
disp(y);
   ]]></programlisting>
</refsection>

